Ad Text:
PeopleSoft Analyst Adelaide CBD | Hybrid (min. 2 days on-site) | Contract to end of June 2026 | Up to $750 per day + Super

About the Role A leading university in Adelaide is seeking an experienced PeopleSoft Analyst to support and enhance its core HR systems during a critical delivery period in early 2026.

Based within the IT HR Systems team and reporting to the Product Manager – HR Systems, this role will support and develop established PeopleSoft platforms that underpin key HR operations across the organisation. You will work closely with HR stakeholders and technical teams to ensure the stability, optimisation and continuous improvement of HCM services supporting staff and student success.

This role is well suited to a hands-on functional specialist who enjoys working across complex HR systems, engaging with stakeholders, and contributing to meaningful outcomes in a large, regulated environment.

Key Responsibilities
Provide functional support for PeopleSoft HCM platforms, including business process support, system configuration and data management.


Analyse business requirements and translate them into effective system solutions and configuration changes.


Support testing and validation activities including system testing, regression testing and user acceptance testing.


Perform data analysis and troubleshooting to resolve system issues and improve data quality.


Work closely with HR business stakeholders, technical teams and vendors to deliver system enhancements and operational support.


Contribute to documentation, process improvement and system optimisation initiatives.


Support ongoing platform stability and continuous improvement initiatives within the HR systems landscape.


Key Skills & Experience Demonstrated experience providing functional support across:


PeopleSoft HCM, including:


Global Payroll


Absence Management


Employee Self Service


Manager Self Service


Time and Labour


Administer Workforce


PeopleSoft Enterprise Learning Management


You will also bring:


Strong experience in process and data management, system configuration, analysis, testing and validation.


Proven ability to work directly with business stakeholders to gather requirements and deliver fit-for-purpose solutions.


Experience working in structured delivery environments (Agile / SCRUM desirable).


Qualifications
Postgraduate qualification (or progress towards) with extensive relevant experience, or


An equivalent combination of relevant professional experience and education / training.


Desirable
Previous experience within a higher education environment.


Experience working in Agile / SCRUM delivery models.


Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills.


Role Details
Contract start: 2 February 2026 (or earlier if available)


Contract end: 26 June 2026


Hours: Full time, 40 hours per week


Location: Adelaide CBD


Hybrid working arrangement – minimum 2 days per week on-site (as agreed with the Hiring Manager)


Contractor to provide own device (laptop)


Weekly timesheet submission required


Participation in after-hours or weekend work may be required


Mandatory shutdown period during December/January (dates advised by the organisation)


Rate: Up to $750 per day + Super

Ad Text:
We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Technical Business Analyst with proven experience in enterprise data platform projects. This role requires a strong analytical mindset, exceptional stakeholder engagement capabilities, and a deep understanding of complex data ecosystems. You will play a key role in driving data migration initiatives, documenting intricate data sources, and supporting the delivery of high-impact data solutions.

In this role you will be responsible for:

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather and analyze business requirements for enterprise data platform initiatives.

Conduct deep dives into source data from a variety of systems, identifying key structures, relationships, and transformation needs.

Document complex data sources with clarity and precision to support development and migration efforts.

Estimate and quantify effort required for data migrations, including source analysis, mapping, and validation.

Engage with stakeholders across multiple business units, managing competing priorities and aligning expectations.

Work with custom SQL datasets and Change Data Capture (CDC) mechanisms to support dynamic data environments.

Apply a working understanding of SQL to validate data, support analysis, and assist in solution design.

Maintain strong customer engagement throughout the project lifecycle, ensuring transparency and alignment.

To be successful in this role your skills and experience should include:

Proven experience as a Business Analyst in enterprise data platform or data migration projects.

Strong customer engagement and communication skills.

Demonstrated ability to analyze and document complex data sources.

Experience with effort estimation for data-related initiatives.

Hands-on experience with custom SQL datasets and CDC (highly desirable).

Solid understanding of SQL and relational data concepts.

Ability to manage multiple stakeholders with varying priorities in a fast-paced environment. 




Benefits
Joining Cognizant will give you the opportunity to learn and collaborate with some of the most talented people in the industry, while having your finger on the pulse of emerging industry trends and working on the cutting edge of technology in your field of expertise. 




We recognize that our people perform at their best when they feel valued as significant contributors and that is why at Cognizant, taking care of our employees is a priority:

You can pursue innovative career tracks and opportunities here

You can enhance your professional development through education and dedicated training 

We’ll give you the skills you need to keep pace with the changing workplace while our compensation, benefits and wellness packages help you stay healthy and plan for the future.

Please reach out to our friendly and welcoming team to apply and register your interest for this full time opportunity with us.

Company Description


Nine is Australia’s largest locally owned media company – the home of Australia’s most trusted and loved brands spanning News, Sport, Lifestyle, and Entertainment. We pride ourselves on creating the best content, accessed by consumers when and how they want – across Publishing, Broadcasting and Digital.

Nine’s assets include the 9Network, major mastheads such as The Sydney Morning Herald, The Age and The Australian Financial Review, radio stations 2GB, 3AW, 4BC and 6PR, digital properties such as nine.com.au, 9Now, 9Honey, Pedestrian.TV, Drive, subscription video platform Stan and a majority investment in Domain Group.

Our Purpose: We shape culture by sparking conversations, challenging perspectives, and entertaining our communities.

We bring people together by celebrating the big occasions and connecting the everyday moments. Australia belongs here. We bring our purpose to life via three shared values: We walk the talk, turn over every stone and keep it human.

Job Description


Nine's Data, Product & Technology - Enterprise team drives commercial growth and deeper engagement with data-driven solutions. As the Data Governance & Privacy Manager, you will be a vital contributor to our responsible data and AI strategy. Working closely with senior leaders, you will help implement and maintain the critical frameworks that allow for ambitious innovation while upholding the highest ethical standards and robust privacy protections. This is a fantastic opportunity to grow your career and make a tangible impact at the forefront of the media industry.

What you’ll do:

Drive Privacy Compliance: You will conduct Privacy Impact Assessments (PIAs) for new projects, ensuring we meet our obligations under the Privacy Act and the APPs.

Manage Risk: You'll help identify and mitigate risks associated with data privacy and the responsible use of AI.

Collaborate and Educate: You will partner with teams across the business to embed a 'Privacy-by-Design' culture and contribute to training programs.

Implement Governance: You'll be hands-on in implementing and maintaining Nine's AI and Data Governance frameworks.

Champion Data Integrity: You will support the management of our key data assets, ensuring their quality and integrity are fit for purpose.

Qualifications


What you’ll bring:

3-5 years of professional experience in data privacy, data governance, or technology risk.

A strong, practical understanding of the Australian Privacy Act 1988 and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs).

Hands-on experience conducting Privacy Impact Assessments (PIAs).

An understanding of data management principles, including data quality and lifecycle management.

A solid grasp of AI concepts (like machine learning and generative AI) and their associated privacy challenges.

Excellent communication skills and a collaborative spirit, with the ability to translate complex ideas into practical advice.

Desirable Skills & Experience

Experience working within the media, entertainment, advertising, or technology industries

Familiarity with data governance rolls and cloud platforms (e.g. Google Cloud Platform)

Familiarity with emerging AI governance, safety, or ethics frameworks.

Relevant industry certifications (CIPM, CIPT, CIPP/E, AIGP)

Additional Information


Our Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion:

We're committed to a safe, respectful and inclusive Nine. From day one, you'll be encouraged to bring your whole self to work and will be supported to perform at your best.

We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disabilities, and of all ages, genders, nationalities, backgrounds and cultures as we recognise the importance and value of diverse perspectives. Should you require any adjustments to the recruitment process, please advise us when you apply.

Work rights: Please note to apply for this role you must already have the right to lawfully work and live in Australia.

Job Title: Head of Financial Planning and Analysis
Ad Text:
About us

For over 150 years, Anglicare Southern Queensland has been walking alongside Queenslanders, offering care, support, and dignity to those who need it most. By providing a range of support services, including aged care, foster care, family support, homelessness services, youth support and counselling, our mission is to make a lasting impact by fostering hope, independence, and inclusion.

At the heart of everything we do is a simple belief: everyone deserves to be treated with dignity, respect, and care. Join our team today, and make a difference today, tomorrow and together. Be where you're needed. Belong right here.

The Role

Anglicare are currently seeking to hire a full-time permanent Head of Financial Planning and Analysis (FPA) to join our Finance team based in our corporate office on Duncan Street, Fortitude Valley. In this role you will support the Chief Financial Officer (CFO) and senior management in delivering Anglicare SQ's Strategic Plan. The position will report directly to the CFO and will provide financial planning and performance support including advice to management and service leaders in understanding and interpreting financial results and performance trends, with particular focus on the longer-term horizon.

The Head of FPA is responsible for the co-ordination and compilation of the budget and forecasting process, management reporting and analysis of profit and loss, capital, cash flow and balance sheet to senior management, the Audit & Risk Committee, and Community Services Commission.

How you will make help us make a difference


Lead the development and delivery of the annual financial planning and budgeting cycle.
Drive the development of longer-term three-way financial projections (5 + years).
Support strategic initiatives including capital planning and digital transformation projects, offering relevant analysis and advice, with focus on delivering financial benefits.
Ensure reporting and analysis dashboards reflects current needs of the organisation and that analysis undertaken will drive longer term thinking.
Support the CFO in financial analysis of strategic initiatives, revenue growth and cost saving opportunities.
Review and interpret the Anglicare financial outcomes (Profit and Loss, Balance Sheet and Cashflow) with particular focus on implications for the longer-term.
Develop and lead a finance partnering team, that aids in delivering positive client outcomes, through provision of constructive financial guidance and advice to service streams.
Drive high performance, through the preparation of team and individual professional development plans, identifying skill gaps and training opportunities.

What our team are looking for


Engaging leader who can build strong relationships, influence and partner strategically with senior leaders in a complex environment.
Experience in the not-for-profit (NFP) or healthcare sector (Ideally)
Degree in Accounting, Business, Finance or similar field, coupled with professional accounting qualifications (CA,CPA,CIMA)
Experience leading and managing team/s in the development of financial plans, including annual budgets, quarterly forecasts and long-term projections within a multi-program organisation.
Experience in transforming FPA teams to enhance partnerships with service streams, adopting new ways of working, and continuously evolving processes and service delivery using best practice and through the use of refined coaching and development skills.
Skilled in managing, guiding, and leading multi-disciplinary teams, fostering a culture of constructive challengers to influence financial outcomes.
Proven experience in developing, analysing, evaluating, and reporting financial outcomes (including metrics) through management and committee papers, interpreting financial information to drive improvements and influence outcomes through advanced problem-solving.
Strong relationship-building skills, together with high-quality written and verbal communication skills, demonstrating effective engagement with diverse stakeholders, influencing and negotiating financial outcomes.
Advanced computer skills, including Microsoft Word/Excel, Workday, and reporting/analytical tools such as PowerBI, D365.

Why you'll love working with Anglicare Southern Queensland


Voted Reader's Digest Most Trusted Brand in Aged Care seven consecutive years in a row.
Know your role is making a real difference supporting Queenslanders in need.
Value-driven organisation rooted in Love, Care, Hope & Humility.
Flexible Working Environment and work from home possibilities.
Not for Profit Salary Packaging (Reduce your taxable income by up to $18,550).
Novated Lease - pay for your car and running costs with pre-tax dollars!
Corporate Health Insurance Discounts with Bupa and Medibank.
Benefits App - discounts and cash back at retailers (Woollies, Big W, Myer & much more!).
Referral App - $1 for each time you share job and up to $300 for a successful referral.
Wellbeing App - Mental, Physical and Financial wellbeing support.
A culture of recognition with our Annual People Awards.
24/7 Employee Assistance Program & Pastoral Care Support.

What's next?

Apply now and send us your most recent CV.

For further information please contact Daniel Walsh - dwalsh @ anglicaresq.org.au

Applications will be progressed as they are received.

Anglicare is committed to building an inclusive and diverse workforce and encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, those from cultural and linguistically diverse backgrounds, LGBTIQ+ communities, people with disabilities and people with a lived experience of mental health issues. We promote a child-safe environment and are committed to providing on- going care and protection.

Cathara Consulting is an Australian-based Consulting firm specialising in Business Transformations and Technology Consulting & Resourcing Services.

Our Northern Territory based client is seeking an experienced Senior Business Analyst to support a high-risk ICT project for an initial, immediate start 6 month contract.

The role:

The Business Analyst will be responsible for a full range of business analysis tasks including requirements planning and management; requirements elicitation, analysis and documentation; and capturing existing business processes and proposed changes. You will be required to support the relevant Project Manager or Director in the execution of the project approach and associated plan working with the business, project team members and the vendor/s as required.

Duties:

Facilitate workshops, interviews, and focus groups with stakeholders to elicit, analyse and document business and functional requirements, and management of requirements traceability.

Conduct walkthroughs to validate and obtain approval of business analysis outputs.

Provide business analysis support relevant to provision of requirements support and clarification throughout a full project development or implementation lifecycle.

Undertake and support testing activities including preparing and executing test plans and cases.

Applying business analysis techniques and tools to document requirements, objectives, outcomes, processes, procedures, work instructions and workflows.

Delivering project documentation in alignment with client project management frameworks, on time, to expected quality standards as per scope and as agreed with the Project Manager.

Managing sensitive information and maintaining records in line with information management policies.

Essential Skills & Experience

Strong experience as a Senior Business Analyst including experience in requirements gathering, business process analysis/modelling, process mapping and information analysis/modelling, planning, design, testing and system integration, using industry standard techniques in a complex business environment.

Experience mapping business requirements and processes to the functionality of a product whilst identifying gaps and opportunities.

High level analytical skills and organisational skills with good attention to detail and ability to think laterally and conceptually.

Highly effective client liaison, change management and facilitation skills.

Demonstrated experience working in a collaborative environment with high performing teams with high priority deliverables under tight timeframes and balancing competing priorities.

Experience in end-to-end delivery of major business systems projects.

Highly skilled in the use of Microsoft Visio and the usual office tools such as Windows, Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Microsoft Outlook (e-mail), proficient in the use of JIRA and SharePoint or ability to quickly acquire.

Experience identifying and analysing complex legislative and / or regulatory requirements applicable to the relevant industry/work environment and their processes.

Desirable Skills and Experience:

Experience in business process model and notation (BPMN) 2.0 standard or similar.

Experience working in a Government environment.

Experience working on education, health or police/frontline services projects would be an advantage


 The successful candidate must be based in or prepared to relocate to Darwin for the term of the contract. No remote or hybrid working options will be accepted.

AEMO at the Heart of Energy 

AEMO is Australia’s independent energy system and market operator and system planner. AEMO’s purpose is to ensure safe, reliable and affordable energy today, and enable the energy transition for the benefit of all Australians.  Australian governments are now committed to a net zero economy for Australia by 2050 and our vision is to enable this. We have the once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to co-design the future of our energy systems, and our core values revolve around character, commitment, and connection. Join us as we contribute to this significant transition in the energy sector.    

About the role  

The Operations division is responsible for operating today’s systems and for market security and reliably, along with supporting AEMO to navigate the energy future. Its Market Management team is responsible for the sound financial management of Australia’s National Electricity Market (NEM), Western Australian Wholesale Electricity Market (WEM) and east coast gas markets with functions including settlement, prudential management, metering and retail market operations. 

Energy markets are in transition and in addition to managing daily operations, the Market Management team are focused on operationalising new rules, systems and processes to support future requirements. As a Senior Energy Analyst, you will be contributing to department strategy and coordinating the design of business processes and systems that support business units through integration and uplift of operational capability.   This new role has been created to provide centralised support for directing team responses in areas including strategy, risk, resource planning, project reporting, contributing to industry forums and internal operational reporting. 

This role can be based anywhere in Australia. 

What you will be doing 

Coordinating, collaborating and leading small groups from operational business units in the Market Management team and broader functional areas within AEMO to identify and resolve a range of strategic and operational challenges.

Collaborating with subject matter experts within the metering, settlement, prudentials or retail markets functions, to participate in and contribute to the identification, assessment and management of complex technical and operational issues and risks.

Undertake analysis and propose options for market/system/process enhancement opportunities that align with AEMO’s strategic direction.

Developing material (eg reports, dashboards and presentations) to inform stakeholders and support decision making. 

What you will bring to the role  

Degree in economics, commerce, engineering, science or a related discipline.

Experience in a commercial, operational or regulatory role in either the Energy or Utility sectors is essential.

Strong facilitation experience in running workshops and taking the lead on problem solving.

Demonstrated experience interpreting technical documents and/or legal instruments, such as rules and regulations in a compliance driven environment.

Proven analytical skills that provide technically resourceful, evidenced based solutions to issues coupled with an ability to effectively communicate proposals and execute solutions in a constructive and timely manner.

Demonstrated ability to develop high quality written reports and deliver effective presentations which communicate technical, complex concepts or data analysis to informed audiences. 

In return some of our benefits to you  

Flexible working: work from home, part time, job share, hybrid options, and additional leave options 

Professional development via projects, industry networks, job rotation, study assistance and more. 

Give back with up to 4 days of volunteering leave per year.  

Reward your hard work with annual performance bonuses (subject to eligibility). 

Embrace a healthier you with our wellness program, discounted health insurance, gym perks and our comprehensive Employee Assistance Program (EAP).  

About Our Process   

At AEMO we are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workforce. We welcome people of all backgrounds, including people with disabilities and neurodivergence and those who identify as Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander. If you have any accessibility requirements to support you during the application or interview process, simply let us know by emailing us at talent@aemo.com.au

Business Analyst | ESG & Emissions Reporting

Location: Balcatta, WA 6021 (Full-time On-site)

Work Type: Contract - Part Time (3 days per week)

Duration: 6 Months +

Rate: Competitive Market Rates

About the Role

We are seeking a proactive Business Analyst to join us at our Balcatta head office. This is a critical, hands-on role focused on the collection, reconciliation, and gap analysis of data required for our end-of-financial-year ESG (Environmental, Social, and Governance) compliance.

This role is strictly on-site, as you will need to work closely with our finance and operations teams to hunt down data and establish new reporting workflows. If you enjoy deep-diving into systems and ensuring legislative compliance, this is a high-impact project for you.

Key Responsibilities

Systems Data Extraction: Navigate Pronto (Finance) and Concur to extract fuel, electricity, and utility invoice data.

Reconciliation: Perform deep-dive reconciliations to ensure quarterly reporting accuracy for emissions legislation.

Gap Analysis: Identify "blind spots" in our emissions data and proactively chase stakeholders on-site to resolve gaps.

Legislative Compliance: Ensure all data aligns with current emissions reporting standards for the end of the financial year.

Process Design: Set up the framework and ongoing management process for ESG data to ensure long-term sustainability.

Skills & Experience Required

Experience: Proven background as a Business Analyst, specifically in data reconciliation, audit, or financial reporting.

Tech Stack: Proficiency in Pronto and Concur is highly desirable.

Proactive Mindset: You are a "chaser" who is comfortable walking the floor and engaging with different departments to find missing information.

Analytical Skills: Advanced Excel skills and the ability to spot anomalies in complex utility and fuel data.

On-site Commitment: Availability to work fully on-site in Balcatta for the duration of the contract.

The Details

Schedule: 3 days per week (On-site in Balcatta).

Start Date: As soon as possible.

Location Benefits: Convenient Balcatta location with free on-site parking (no CBD traffic or parking fees).


Please reach out to Joseph Demetriou - joseph.demetriou(@)aurec.com for a confidential discussion about the role and its requirements.

Job Title: Executive General Manager - Data, Tech & Digital Transformation
Ad Text:
About the TIO

The Telecommunications Industry Ombudsman (TIO) is an independent, not-for-profit organisation that provides fair, accessible and effective dispute resolution services for consumers and members in Australia’s communications sector. Guided by strong values of fairness, integrity, collaboration and excellence, TIO plays a critical role in improving industry practices, influencing public debate and maintaining trust in a rapidly evolving communications and digital landscape.

TIO is embarking on a significant phase of data, technology and digital transformation, with a clear focus on partnering with and enabling its operational teams. This transformation is central to improving end-to-end complaint handling, strengthening insight and decision-making, and ensuring systems, processes and capabilities are fit for purpose now and into the future.

About the role

Reporting to the Ombudsman, the Executive General Manager – Data, Technology and Digital Transformation leads TIO’s enterprise technology, data and analytics, digital transformation, cybersecurity and emerging AI capability. The role is accountable for setting and delivering an integrated technology and data strategy that supports operational performance, service quality and organisational resilience.

As a key member of the Executive Leadership Team, you will work in close partnership with executive peers, particularly across operations to translate strategy into delivery, modernise systems and processes, and embed strong governance, change management and capability uplift across the organisation.

About You

You will be a senior executive with a proven track record leading data, technology and digital transformation in complex, service-oriented environments. You bring the ability to lead technical specialists while engaging credibly at executive and board level, translating complexity into clear strategic direction and practical outcomes.

You will be a collaborative, values-led leader with strong commercial judgement, experience delivering enterprise change within constrained resources, and a demonstrated ability to build high-performing, inclusive teams. Experience in public, regulatory or purpose-driven organisations will be highly regarded, as will a pragmatic, risk-aware approach to innovation and AI enablement.

 

 

Hazel Executive & Boards is pleased to be partnering with the Telecommunications Industry Ombudsman (TIO) on this Executive General Manager search and appointment process. All direct and third-party applications will be forwarded to Hazel.

Hazel acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of the lands on which we live and work. We pay our respects to Elders past and present. We are committed to fostering equal opportunity and championing diversity, inclusion, belonging, flexibility, and accessibility in all that we do. If you require any adjustments in engaging with us or as part of a recruitment process, please let us know so we can support you.




To review the Briefing Pack please go to the Hazel Executive website where it can be downloaded off the link at the bottom of the advertisement.




Applications can be made directly via the Hazel Executive & Boards website – www.hazelexecutive.com.au

Company Description


Lendi Group is a market-leading digital platform business that is focused on revolutionising the entire property journey. It operates Lendi - Australia’s original and #1 digital mortgage brand - and the iconic Aussie franchise.

Powered by an advanced AI proprietary platform, a national network of 1,300 brokers, 230 retail stores, a team of experienced buyer’s agents, integrated property search and conveyancing, Aussie is supporting customers at every step of their property journey to find, buy and own with more confidence than ever before. Lendi Group’s loan book is more than $100b and it was named Australia’s Aggregator of the Year for 2024.

To learn more about life at Lendi Group check out our blog: https://www.lendi.com.au/inspire/category/life-at-lendi/

Why Join Us?

Innovation at Our Core – We challenge the status quo and push boundaries to create better solutions.
Work with the Best – Collaborate with some of the brightest minds in fintech, financial services, and strategy.
Make an Impact – Contribute to meaningful projects that shape our business and the future of property finance.
Grow & Evolve – Develop your skills and advance your career in a fast-moving, purpose-driven environment.

As a Lead Data Scientist, you'll lead a growing data science team and play a pivotal role in shaping and delivering data-driven solutions across stakeholders. Your primary responsibilities include leading and mentoring your team, designing and implementing advanced machine learning and statistical models, translating complex business problems into scalable data products, and leading the end-to-end lifecycle from discovery to production. You will lead by example with modern data science techniques and tooling, providing clear technical direction and coaching to team members. 

We’re looking for a collaborative team player who thrives in a dynamic environment, embraces the challenge of legacy systems, remains composed under pressure, and is driven to deliver continuous improvement and strategic impact.  This role provides a unique opportunity to connect directly with our stakeholders.  You should be a versatile data leader who can both drive hands-on delivery and lead the development of new data initiatives—balancing strategic oversight with practical execution. 

Job Description


On a typical day you will: 
 

Lead, mentor and motivate a data science team (up to10 people) and set the technical direction and standards 
Collaborate within a cross-functional digital team, including Product Management, Engineering and Design. 
Bridge the gap between business problems and data science solutions, turning opportunities into impactful, production-ready models. 
Utilise strong analytical and modelling skills to design, build, and validate machine learning solutions, particularly tree-based methods (e.g. XGBoost, GBM, LightGBM), neural networks, and transformer-based approaches. 
Define and lead the end-to-end lifecycle of data products in an agile environment, from problem framing and experimentation through to deployment and monitoring. 
Conduct and document detailed analysis, including business case development, to prioritise use cases and clearly communicate trade-offs and expected value to stakeholders. 
Work closely with data and platform engineers on ETL pipelines, containerised solutions (e.g. Docker, Kubernetes), and cloud-based environments (e.g. GCP, AWS, Azure), with exposure to modern data platforms such as Snowflake and Databricks. 
Collaborate with cross-functional Agile teams (Engineering, Product, Design, QA) in remote and on-site settings, applying appropriate governance and engagement models to data projects. 
Provide BAU support for existing models and data products, while actively managing demand, prioritisation, and stakeholder expectations to create space for strategic, high-impact data science initiatives. 

Qualifications


Proven end-to-end Data Science experience (6+ years), including recent experience operating at Senior/Lead level 
Proven ability to lead, mentor and motivate a data science team (typically 3–10 people) and to set technical direction and standards 
Strong, hands-on expertise with modern machine learning models and algorithms, particularly tree-based methods (e.g. XGBoost, GBM, LightGBM), statistical models, and neural networks 
Demonstrated experience working with LLMs, transformers and embeddings in practical, production-oriented use cases 
Solid understanding of the end-to-end lifecycle of data products, from problem framing and model development through to productisation, pipelining and BAU support 
Proficiency in Python and a strong command of SQL for data exploration, feature engineering and model implementation 
Experience working with cloud platforms (e.g. GCP, AWS or Azure) and familiarity with modern data ecosystems such as Snowflake and/or Databricks (or ability to upskill quickly) 
Exposure to containerised solutions (e.g. Docker) and collaborating with engineers on production deployment and MLOps practices 
Strong stakeholder management and communication skills, with the ability to translate business problems into data solutions and tell a compelling story with insights 
Experience contributing to or leading governance and engagement models (e.g. steering committees, RACI/RASCI frameworks, working groups) across multiple stakeholders 
Demonstrated capability in prioritisation and managing tradeoffs in a resourceconstrained or scaleup environment, including pushing back on lowvalue work 
Experience developing or contributing to business cases for data and AI initiatives, including articulating value, risks and assumptions 

Additional Information


Lendi Group teams operate across Australia and the Philippines. Bringing together diverse expertise, innovative technology and a customer-first approach, our teams work seamlessly to simplify the property journey, helping Australians find, buy and own property with confidence.

We support our people in a variety of ways, but a few of the benefits that our people rave about include:

A vibrant, relaxed, yet professional culture.
Hybrid working arrangement designed to support work-life balance, while fostering meaningful connection and collaboration.
A holistic wellbeing programs offering 24/7 support, including medical, mental health, and financial wellbeing services to enable our workforce to thrive at home and work.
Generous paid Parental Leave: we celebrate our growing Lendi Group family with 18-26 weeks leave for primary carers and up to 4 weeks for secondary carers.
An additional week’s Loyalty Leave each year after reaching 3 years’ service.
Wellness initiatives with a strong focus on psychological safety.

We’re committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive community at Lendi Group. We believe that a team reflecting the world around us leads to greater innovation, stronger collaboration, and a more engaging workplace.

Our culture is guided by our 3 core values: We Are Stronger United; Act Like You Own It; and Keep Home Loans Human. Our values are part of our core DNA that helps Lendi Group to attract, engage and evolve the right talent and build best-in-class products.

This is an opportunity to shape the future of a fast-growing, purpose-driven company that’s transforming the homeownership journey.

Ready to contribute to Lendi Group’s next chapter? Apply now and be part of something big!

As an Engagement Lead, you will shape the future of how organisations use AI to create meaningful human experiences and business value. You will have the opportunity to lead transformative engagements, guide talented multidisciplinary teams, and influence the strategic direction of our clients and our own practice

Your Role and Responsibilities

As an Engagement Lead, you will operate at the intersection of delivery, product strategy and management, and client success . You will lead multidisciplinary teams that include strategists, designers, technologists, and data scientists to deliver transformative outcomes for clients. You will be accountable for the success of client engagements - from inception and vision through to implementation and measurable business impact.

You will bring a strong commercial mindset, deep understanding of human-centered design and AI-enabled transformation, and the ability to advise senior client stakeholders on how to reimagine their businesses for the future.

Hybrid ways of working

We are looking for an enthusiastic and proactive Senior Data Scientist to join our dynamic team. BTI Executive Search are advertising this role on behalf of our client, EXL Service Australia Pty Ltd, a global analytics and digital solutions company delivering tailored AI and data-driven solutions across multiple industries. EXL partners with leading organisations across insurance, healthcare, banking and capital markets, retail, media and communications, and energy and infrastructure to help reimagine business models, deliver measurable outcomes, and accelerate innovation.

EXL Service is currently seeking a qualified and experienced Senior Consultant specialising in Generative AI & MLOps to support key client within the Banking and Financial Services sector.

This is a full-time, permanent position based in Melbourne, Victoria.

Key Responsibilities:
Establish and deploy AI-driven solutions tailored to internal audit, compliance, and risk control functions, focusing on automation of manual processes through Generative AI, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), and LLM orchestration frameworks.
Design, develop, and manage scalable ML pipelines using Google Cloud Vertex AI, enabling secure, reproducible model deployment across UAT and production environments under SOC2-compliant frameworks.
Build and operationalize real-time model monitoring and drift detection systems using Prometheus and custom alerting logic, ensuring regulatory-grade reliability of deployed models.
Lead the implementation of containerized CI/CD pipelines (Docker, Kubernetes, Cloud Build) for secure model versioning, auditability, and enterprise DevOps compliance.
Optimize training and inference workflows on GPU infrastructure (e.g., NVIDIA A10G), applying TensorFlow and CUDA to meet performance SLAs for high-volume risk and control use cases.
Collaborate with risk, data governance, and compliance stakeholders to integrate AI solutions with enterprise-wide audit protocols, reduce manual oversight, and align with internal review policies.
Deliver end-to-end MLOps lifecycle management—from structured/semi-structured data ingestion (Pandas, Spark) through to model tuning, evaluation, retraining, and audit traceability.
Drive internal research pilots focused on multi-agent LLM orchestration (LangChain, Pinecone) including memory management, agentic task planning, and secure enterprise knowledge retrieval.
Support the development of benchmarking frameworks to assess control maturity, RCA quality, and AI/ML performance across internal divisions and business units.
Required Qualification and Experience:
6–10 years of experience across AI/ML systems, enterprise IT, and risk/regulatory environments (financial services preferred).
Post-Graduation in Data Science, Information Systems, or Business Analytics.
Domain exposure in Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC), MLOps, and regulatory reporting (e.g., Basel, APRA).
Required Skills and Attributes:
Strong ability to design and present technical solutions aligned with internal risk frameworks, security protocols, and regulatory controls.
Demonstrated stakeholder engagement experience across compliance, audit, and IT leadership functions.
Broad expertise in AI system architecture, CI/CD workflows, and observability tooling (e.g., Prometheus, MLflow).
Advanced knowledge of Python-based data and ML stacks including TensorFlow, Pandas, NumPy, Spark.
Working experience in programming secure LLM workflows and vector-based retrieval systems using LangChain, Pinecone, and GPT APIs.
Hands-on knowledge of GCP components (Vertex AI, BigQuery, Cloud Build, GKE).
Analytical thinking, problem-solving, and ability to work autonomously in high-accountability environments.
How to apply:
If you meet the requirements, you can apply directly via SEEK or email your CV to jasmine.kad@btiexecutivesearch.com.au

We are seeking an experienced Business Analyst to support a finance transformation that will migrate NobleOak from being a Friendly Society to a Life Insurance Company. 

This is a business-focused role with some technology requirements. It is suited to someone who has domain knowledge and a proven track record of delivering change across finance processes, reporting, and controls.
The successful candidate will play a key role in shaping and delivering improvements to processes, and systems, working closely with the Finance team and stakeholders to drive meaningful transformation.




Key Accountabilities

Project Stream Lead – Work closely with CFO and Finance Team Leaders to project manage the finance stream of the project whilst facilitating and prioritising process improvement opportunities across the Finance function.
Business & System Requirements Gathering – Work with various stakeholder to determine what is the issue that needs solving and business needs that need to be met as part of the resolution. 
Analysis & Diagnostics – Conduct & analyse existing systems, applications, and processes to identify areas of inefficiency or potential improvements. Perform root cause analysis to determine the underlying issues and provide actionable recommendations for enhancing system performance, usability, and reliability. 
Planning – Identifying required activities, document activities, define dependent activities/links to other projects, and working with relevant departments to ensure activities are carried out efficiently and effectively.
Process Documentation – Support the Finance team with development of process registers and process documentation.
Reporting – Optimise the Chart of Accounts (COA) and proposed postings to align with the LifeCo structure, ensuring all reporting requirements are met for management, partners, and external regulators. Reengineer the cost allocation model to allocate costs to products effectively, simplifying where possible. 


Key Responsibilities

Partner with Finance teams to analyse, document, and optimise business processes and workflows.
Lead requirements gathering and process mapping for finance transformation initiatives (e.g., GL, reporting, reconciliations, controls).
Define and document current-state and target-state processes, identifying improvement opportunities.
Collaborate with stakeholders to ensure business needs are captured and solutions are fit-for-purpose.
Support delivery and implementation of finance process and system changes (in partnership with technology where needed).
Develop and maintain business documentation including BRDs, process maps, test scripts, and training materials.
Support UAT, business readiness, and post-implementation review activities.
Provide actionable insights and recommendations to enhance finance efficiency and accuracy.



Capabilities

Proven and extensive business analysis expertise, preferably within the Life Insurance industry or financial services sector.
Excellent planning, presenting and implementation skills.
Understanding of finance operations, procedures and policies related to the insurance industry. 
Master of core BA disciplines, including requirements elicitation and management, process mapping (As-Is/To-Be), gap analysis, and creating detailed business requirements documentation.
Excellent communication (both written and verbal) and time management skills.
High level of interpersonal and stakeholder management skills.
Highly motivated with the ability to work without direct supervision.
Proven ability to provide technical & operational solutions. 
Independent and proactive drive: a proactive self-starter who demonstrates strong initiative and a drive to achieve successful outcomes.

Experience & Qualifications

Extensive Business Analysis experience.

Solution Architect - Data and Integration.

Join a leading organisation driving digital transformation across both corporate IT and operational technology environments. As the Data and Integration Architect, you'll play a pivotal role in shaping and implementing scalable, secure, and future-ready architecture that supports critical business operations, analytics, and decision-making.

Location: Sydney (Hybrid work flexibility)
Reporting to: Enterprise Architecture Lead
Dotted Line Reporting: Group Manager, Enterprise Data & Analytics
Team Size: No direct reports
Industry: Mining / Utilities / Infrastructure

About the Role

This is a senior architecture role responsible for defining and guiding enterprise-wide data and integration architecture across a complex, asset-intensive environment.

You'll work closely with Enterprise Architecture, Data & Analytics, Engineering, and business stakeholders to ensure data flows securely and reliably across operational systems, integration platforms, and analytics layers - from source systems through to reporting and insight.

The role also plays a key part in architecture governance, contributing to the Architecture Review Board (ARB), uplifting data maturity, and acting as a trusted advisor on integration strategy, data governance, security, and emerging technologies, including AI enablement.

Key Responsibilities
Define and maintain enterprise data and integration architecture frameworks, standards, and reference patterns.
Design and govern scalable integration solutions, including APIs, event-based integration, and data pipelines across cloud and on-prem environments.
Provide architectural oversight across platforms including Boomi, Databricks, Microsoft Fabric, Power BI, and Coalesce.
Ensure strong alignment between integration, analytics, and reporting layers, including Power BI semantic models and enterprise reporting standards.
Champion data governance, metadata, lineage, and lifecycle management, supporting the rollout of a formal Data Governance platform (e.g. Alation or KADA).
Guide delivery teams to ensure solutions meet security, compliance, and architectural standards.
Contribute to ARB decisions and architecture assurance across integration and data initiatives.
Evaluate and advise on emerging technologies, including API strategy, MCPs, and AI-ready architecture patterns.
Collaborate across IT, OT, and business teams, balancing strategic intent with practical delivery.
Mentor engineers and designers, supporting capability uplift across data and integration disciplines.
Technology Environment

This organisation is an Azure-first environment, with a modern data and integration stack including:

Integration: Boomi (core), APIs, event-based patterns
Data & Analytics: Databricks, Microsoft Fabric, Coalesce
Reporting & BI: Power BI (models and reports)
Cloud & Platform: Microsoft Azure
Low-Code / Automation: Power Apps, Power Automate
Data Governance (incoming): Alation or KADA

Knowledge of API design, integration patterns, and AI-forward architectures will be highly regarded as the platform continues to evolve.

What We're Looking For
Tertiary qualifications in IT, Computer Science, or a related discipline.
Strong experience in data and integration architecture within complex enterprise environments.
Hands-on architectural knowledge across integration platforms, data pipelines, analytics platforms, and reporting layers.
Experience working in asset-intensive or operational environments (e.g. utilities, infrastructure, mining) is highly desirable.
Strong understanding of data governance, metadata, and architecture assurance.
Ability to influence and operate effectively within a matrixed reporting structure.
Experience uplifting architecture capability in low-to-mid data maturity environments.
Certifications such as TOGAF, DAMA CDMP, or Microsoft Azure credentials are advantageous.

Open to step-up candidates:

We are open to experienced Solution Designers or early-career Solution Architects looking to step into an enterprise architecture role, provided they come from a mature architecture environment and hold TOGAF certification. Strong mentoring support will be provided by the EA Lead.

Additional Information
Occasional travel to regional sites may be required; a driver's licence and access to a vehicle would be beneficial.
This role offers strong visibility, influence, and the opportunity to shape how data and integration architecture comes to life at scale.

Role:

Data Scientist

About Us

We are a fast-growing women’s fashion company with strong retail and wholesale operations. Our business is data-driven and continuously evolving, and we rely on analytics to support planning, buying, inventory management and financial decision-making.

As we expand, we are seeking a hands-on Data Scientist who can combine technical expertise with commercial insight to help us build smarter, more efficient processes and deliver actionable insights across the business.




Role Purpose:


The Data Scientist will enable data-driven decision making across the business by developing predictive models, automating data workflows and delivering analytical insights.           This is both a technical and business facing role, working closely with Retail, Ecommerce, Manufacturing, Merchandising and Finance teams to improve planning, reporting, system automation, integration and commercial performance. The role requires strong coding capability, the ability to integrate data across multiple business systems and the skill to translate complex analytical outputs into clear, actionable recommendations. You will also contribute to maintaining and enhancing our reporting/analytics platform to ensure it evolves with business needs.




Key Responsibilities:




Develop automated data pipelines, analytics tools and reporting solutions using production quality code.

Streamline business processes to improve efficiency and analysis to support sales forecasting, planning and inventory optimisation.

Code and maintain data integrations between various business systems (eg: ERP, POS, E-commerce, TM1, Planning, BI).

Maintain and enhance existing planning and analytics models to support new requirements and business growth.

Collect, clean, structure and integrate datasets from multiple internal and external sources.

Partner with cross-functional teams to translate business questions into data-driven methodologies and insights.

Develop dashboards and visualisations to support performance tracking and commercial decision making.

Communicate analytical findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders in clear, business-relevant language.

Ensure data governance, quality, and integrity within analytical processes and platforms.

Research and adopt new data science techniques and technologies to enhance analytical capability.

Required Skills & Experience:

Strong programming ability in Python (or a similar language) for modelling, automation, and integrations.

Proficiency in SQL for data manipulation, querying, and pipeline development.

Experience applying machine learning or statistical modelling to real business problems.

Experience coding integrations between different systems, APIs and data sources.

Strong analytical and problem-solving capability with attention to detail.

Attributes:

Commercially minded with strong business awareness.

Curious and proactive approach to problem-solving.

Able to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams.

Comfortable operating with autonomy and end-to-end ownership.




What We Offer

Competitive salary

Work globally with a dedicated team of passionate professionals.

Generous staff discounts

Quarterly company gift cards 

Development & Recognition opportunities

Positive company culture

Vibrant and happy work environment

Opportunity to work in a fast-paced, creative industry.

Collaborative and supportive team environment.

Why Join Us?

High-impact role influencing retail, wholesale and financial decisions

Opportunity to shape the company’s data and analytics capabilities

Work closely with leadership in a data-first environment

Fast-paced, collaborative team with strong growth potential

If you are passionate about coding, analytics and creating data-driven impact across retail and wholesale environments, we’d love to hear from you.

The National Manager, Data Products is a senior leadership role at the forefront of DFR's data-led transformation. You will own the vision, strategy, and roadmap for Data, Analytics, AI, and BI products, ensuring they deliver measurable impact and align with enterprise goals. Working closely with senior leaders, ADF executives, and business stakeholders, you'll embed data into core workflows, turning complex information into trusted, high-value products that accelerate decision-making. Leading a high-performing team, you'll drive cultural uplift with data, foster adoption, and establish a data product operating model that supports DFR's mission and strategic objectives.

Details about the Client

ADF Careers is the largest workforce outsourcing solution in the southern hemisphere with over 80,000 applications received on average each year.
ADF Careers is on a mission to recruit the right people, in the right numbers, at the right time to support the Australian Defence Force to build, sustain and maximise Defence capability.


Our people are our greatest asset. We recognise and respect our people's need to work in ways that support their careers, families, and lifestyle. That's why we offer flexible working arrangements, learning pathways, additional leave entitlements and extensive corporate discounts across a variety of product and services. We want our people to be financially rewarded; to feel good and to go beyond what they thought possible at work.

Be you, and we'll be better together.

To find out more about our great employee benefits and what it's like to be part of the team, reach out to our friendly talent acquisition team.

Job Description

The National Manager Data Products is responsible for driving the data-led transformation journey - owning the vision, roadmap, prioritisation, success, and adoption of Data, Analytics, AI, Business Intelligence, and Data Visualisation products - enabling key DFR functional areas to make smarter, faster, data driven decisions in support of the DFR mission and purpose.

This role sits at the intersection of impact, adoption, and data. You'll work closely with key leaders across functional domains, including head of functions, ADF executives, and business stakeholders to ensure that DFR's data products directly contribute and support achievement of all relevant KPIs for Adecco DFR.

You will:

Own the whole of business data vision, strategy, and roadmap for DFR data products, ensuring an enterprise lens that aligns data transformation to DFR's key enterprise goals.
Define and measure success, linking data product outcomes to DFR enterprise goals.
Manage the end-to-end product lifecycle, from discovery, experimentation, delivery, adoption, and embedding into business workflows.
Embed data led initiatives as a core value and shared accountability across leaders and teams
Prioritise new opportunities (impact, effort, risk) by deeply understanding our stakeholders and monitoring emerging opportunities and challenges.
Establish a data product marketplace as a familiar resource for discovering, understanding, and selecting data products to meet data consumers' needs.
Partner with internal stakeholders using design thinking to increase adoption of data products and enhance feedback loops and mechanisms.
Deliver technical and cultural uplift, adoption and facilitate methods to diagnose current state barriers and shape a data products operating model to achieve DFRs enterprise goals
Communicate strategy, progress, and outcomes clearly to all levels, from delivery teams to executives.
Identifying opportunities to productise data and leverage data assets to improve new and existing features that exceed our customers' expectations.​
Adhere to relevant Defence, Commonwealth, and Domain specific policies and procedures. ​
Maintain strong stakeholder relationships, delivering strategic advice and guiding them through their Data and AI journeys

Candidate's Profile

If you have worked in a similar position or just looking for your next opportunity that will make an impact, we want to speak with you.

Your background will demonstrate:

8+ years' experience driving cross-functional transformation across executive, operational, leadership, and front-line teams
6+ years' experience managing and leading teams
6+ years of experience working in complex, regionally distributed organisations, with a track record of delivery and excellence
Skilled at facilitating co-design of solutions, and securing adoption across executives, leaders, and frontline colleagues, including relevant diagnosis of blockers and challenges
Proven ability to lead cross functional transformation, translating strategic goals into data products, with stable and measurable delivery roadmaps.
Detail-oriented with strong organisational, storytelling, project management skills, with the ability to prioritise tasks and meet deadlines.
Resilient and adaptable mindset, with the ability to thrive in a fast-paced and ever-changing environment.
Ability to effectively communicate with multiple functions and stakeholders within a nationally dispersed environment.
Demonstrated people leadership capability, including coaching and developing a high performing team
Bachelor's Degree in IT, Data, Change, Communications, or Business​

To apply for this position, you must be an Australian citizen and have the ability to maintain an Australian AGSVA security clearance.

How to apply

If eligible, please submit your resume; applications are open to all qualified Australian citizens.

If you need assistance during our recruitment process, please email Victoria Emms at victoria.emms@adecco.com.au for a confidential conversation.

To apply for this position, please submit your application online through our designated platform. The deadline for applications is 11:30 PM (AEST) on Wednesday 28th January. It's important to note that applications will be reviewed and processed as they are received.

Job Description

The National Manager Data Products is responsible for driving the data-led transformation journey - owning the vision, roadmap, prioritisation, success, and adoption of Data, Analytics, AI, Business Intelligence, and Data Visualisation products - enabling key DFR functional areas to make smarter, faster, data driven decisions in support of the DFR mission and purpose.

This role sits at the intersection of impact, adoption, and data. You'll work closely with key leaders across functional domains, including head of functions, ADF executives, and business stakeholders to ensure that DFR's data products directly contribute and support achievement of all relevant KPIs for Adecco DFR.

You will:

Own the whole of business data vision, strategy, and roadmap for DFR data products, ensuring an enterprise lens that aligns data transformation to DFR's key enterprise goals.
Define and measure success, linking data product outcomes to DFR enterprise goals.
Manage the end-to-end product lifecycle, from discovery, experimentation, delivery, adoption, and embedding into business workflows.
Embed data led initiatives as a core value and shared accountability across leaders and teams
Prioritise new opportunities (impact, effort, risk) by deeply understanding our stakeholders and monitoring emerging opportunities and challenges.
Establish a data product marketplace as a familiar resource for discovering, understanding, and selecting data products to meet data consumers' needs.
Partner with internal stakeholders using design thinking to increase adoption of data products and enhance feedback loops and mechanisms.
Deliver technical and cultural uplift, adoption and facilitate methods to diagnose current state barriers and shape a data products operating model to achieve DFRs enterprise goals
Communicate strategy, progress, and outcomes clearly to all levels, from delivery teams to executives.
Identifying opportunities to productise data and leverage data assets to improve new and existing features that exceed our customers' expectations.​
Adhere to relevant Defence, Commonwealth, and Domain specific policies and procedures. ​
Maintain strong stakeholder relationships, delivering strategic advice and guiding them through their Data and AI journeys

Candidate's Profile

If you have worked in a similar position or just looking for your next opportunity that will make an impact, we want to speak with you.

Your background will demonstrate:

8+ years' experience driving cross-functional transformation across executive, operational, leadership, and front-line teams
6+ years' experience managing and leading teams
6+ years of experience working in complex, regionally distributed organisations, with a track record of delivery and excellence
Skilled at facilitating co-design of solutions, and securing adoption across executives, leaders, and frontline colleagues, including relevant diagnosis of blockers and challenges
Proven ability to lead cross functional transformation, translating strategic goals into data products, with stable and measurable delivery roadmaps.
Detail-oriented with strong organisational, storytelling, project management skills, with the ability to prioritise tasks and meet deadlines.
Resilient and adaptable mindset, with the ability to thrive in a fast-paced and ever-changing environment.
Ability to effectively communicate with multiple functions and stakeholders within a nationally dispersed environment.
Demonstrated people leadership capability, including coaching and developing a high performing team
Bachelor's Degree in IT, Data, Change, Communications, or Business​

To apply for this position, you must be an Australian citizen and have the ability to maintain an Australian AGSVA security clearance.

How to apply

If eligible, please submit your resume; applications are open to all qualified Australian citizens.

If you need assistance during our recruitment process, please email Victoria Emms at victoria.emms@adecco.com.au for a confidential conversation.

To apply for this position, please submit your application online through our designated platform. The deadline for applications is 11:30 PM (AEST) on Wednesday 28th January. It's important to note that applications will be reviewed and processed as they are received.

Bring your brilliance to the Department for Education as our new Director, Strategic Data Initiatives. This is a pivotal leadership role at the centre of strategy, schools, and systemic improvement.

You'll lead major data initiatives that directly empower schools and preschools to leverage insights for improvement, while feeding grassroots intelligence back into the system to strengthen public education statewide.

Why work with us:

Every child and young person deserves a great education.

We have a strategy that aims to unlock every child’s potential now and into the future, one that in partnership with learners, students, parents, and the wider South Australian community will build a world-leading public education system. One that is equitable and prioritises learning and wellbeing.

Together we will make our education system the best it can be.

When our children and young people thrive, so do our communities and our state.

About the role:

The Director, Strategic Data Initiatives leads major strategic data initiatives led by the Strategy and Performance division, playing the critical role of working with schools and preschools to leverage data insights for improvement, and providing school and preschool insights back into the system for systemic improvement of public education.

Reporting to the Executive Director, Strategy and Performance, the role develops and coordinates strategic advice and policy input requested from Strategy and Performance for the Executive Director. They will also work closely with schools and preschools to lead the development and implementation of the Department’s Data Capability Strategy and provide tools, advice and practical supports for schools and preschools to become evidence informed and strategically aligned to the needs of their community, through data driven approaches.

About the team:

The Strategy and Performance Division works across the Department for Education to facilitate best practice strategy and policy development and coordinate a strategic approach to stakeholder engagement, media and communications. The Division positions public education for success, manages strategic risks, provides insights and supports schools and preschools to succeed in the eyes of their communities.

The Strategic Data Initiatives directorate leads key departmental strategic initiatives that Strategy and Performance has ownership of, including primary responsibility for wellbeing data collection and analysis, data capability, and data literacy initiatives. The team also coordinates Strategy and Performance’s participation in national projects, research activities, and priority reforms, provides project management support to the division, and leads the division’s policy function.

About you:

Proven leader who builds high-performing teams and drives continuous improvement through strategic, values-based management.

Strong interpersonal and negotiation skills with demonstrated success achieving change through collaboration and influence.

High-level political acumen and understanding of State and Commonwealth government landscapes.

Track record in business strategy, transformation, and delivering strategic operational advice.

Passionate about developing staff while maintaining accountability and performance standards.

Excellent communication, analytical, and research skills with ability to synthesize complex information.

Flexible, resilient, and politically astute with strong critical thinking abilities.

Essential qualifications and competencies:

An appropriate tertiary qualification including post-graduate qualifications in an appropriate discipline desirable or relevant experience

Experience leading in a large and complex organisation at a senior level, ensuring the translation of priorities into executed deliverables.

You must have, or be able to obtain, a Department for Human Resources issued Working With Children Check

Enquiries:

Enquiries can be directed to Luke Fraser, Executive Director, Strategy and Performance, via email: Luke.Fraser3@sa.gov.au

How to apply:

Applications should be made through the I Work For SA website.

For further information including position locations, and details on how to apply for this vacancy, please go to iworkfor.sa.gov.au and search for vacancy number 713990

Job Title: Head of Business Process Data and Analytics
Ad Text:
This is: the job
This is a permanent Senior Leadership role responsible for shaping how business processes, master data, and analytics are governed and leveraged across a large, complex organisation. Sitting at the intersection of Finance, IT, and operations, this role owns the enterprise process landscape and the reporting platforms that underpin critical decision-making.

You’ll lead a multi-disciplinary team responsible for business process governance, master data management, and enterprise reporting, with a strong focus on standardisation, continuous improvement, and data-driven outcomes. This role offers the opportunity to build structure, capability, and influence at scale.

Based in Melbourne, this position works closely with Executive Leadership and Senior stakeholders across the business, ensuring processes and insights enable efficient operations, compliance, and long-term growth.

This is: what you’ll do
Lead the strategic direction for business process management, master data governance, and enterprise analytics
Own and maintain the end-to-end process architecture
Govern the business process community of practice, appointing and supporting process owners across the business
Drive continuous improvement initiatives to enhance process efficiency, system performance, and user experience
Lead, mentor, and develop a team of analysts and data professionals across process, data, and reporting streams
Oversee master data governance, including policies, controls, and bulk change procedures within systems of record
Manage the enterprise analytics platform, including Power BI, data pipelines, and governed reporting outputs
Partner closely with IT, finance, operations, supply chain, and commercial teams to align processes with strategy
Manage vendor relationships and external service providers to ensure quality delivery and value
Own budget management and performance reporting for the function, using data-driven insights to guide decisions

This is: what you’ll need
10+ years’ experience in business process management, data, or enterprise analytics leadership roles
Proven experience operating in complex, enterprise or manufacturing environments
Strong leadership capability with experience managing and developing cross-functional teams
Deep understanding of ERP-centric process and data landscapes and associated core applications
Advanced experience with business intelligence and analytics platforms, particularly Power BI
Demonstrated ability to engage senior stakeholders and influence at executive level
Strong analytical, problem-solving, and decision-making skills
Experience working in global or multi-site organisations is highly regarded

This is: the perks
High visibility and direct engagement with executive leadership
Opportunity to shape governance, capability, and future ways of working
Work at the intersection of process, data, and strategy at scale
Create a future vision across data analytics, business process, and master data management

About Alberts

Alberts offers a premium hybrid workplace for businesses seeking to enhance their company culture. With a revolutionary office leasing model and private members work club, Alberts is home to aspirational workspaces, enhanced shared facilities and exceptional amenities. With properties located across seven central locations, Alberts inspires a community of Auckland's most ambitious minds and innovative businesses who can network and connect at Alberts events in our beautifully curated spaces.

We are currently expanding the Alberts model into Australia.

The Opportunity

We are seeking an experienced Fund Management Analyst to support our management team in the financial and strategic oversight of property investment funds. This role is responsible for delivering accurate and insightful analysis, preparing investor reporting, and assisting in the ongoing monitoring of fund performance, asset valuations, and capital management.

This is a dynamic analyst role offering variety and impact within a fast-paced, high-performing environment. No two days will be the same.

The role will work across a broad range of business activities from day-to-day operational optimisation to high impact strategic initiatives working closely with senior management.

Success in this role requires strong analytical skills, commercial acumen, and a proactive approach to problem solving. The ideal candidate will be resilient, adaptable, and an effective communicator, able to manage competing priorities and navigate complex stakeholder relationships while maintaining focus and balance under pressure.

What You'll Be Doing

Drive financial performance by updating and analysing development feasibilities and scenario models.

Evaluate new development and investment opportunities through robust financial analysis and due diligence coordination.

Prepare clear, compelling investment reports and recommendations for internal and external stakeholders.

Manage banking processes, including satisfaction of conditions precedent and coordination of loan documentation.

Deliver market and company insights through targeted research and maintenance of key data sets.

Monitor and report on fund and asset performance, providing actionable insights to senior management.

What You'll Bring

Bachelor's degree in finance, Commerce, Economics, Accounting, or related field (CFA/CA/CPA preferred but not essential).

2–4 years' experience in funds management, investment banking, corporate finance, property, or related financial services.

Advanced financial modelling and Excel skills, with strong quantitative analysis capabilities.

Solid understanding of investment principles, property markets, and valuation methodologies.

Proven ability to create high-quality investor reports, presentations, and pitch decks (advanced PowerPoint skills essential).

Knowledge of debt and equity structures in property funds is highly regarded.

Strong attention to detail, organisational skills, and a collaborative, solutions focused mindset, with the ability to thrive under pressure in dynamic and evolving business environment.

Why Join Alberts?

Be part of a visionary company shaping the future of workspaces

Gain exposure to all facets of fund management, from daily business optimisation to transformative strategic projects.

Learn from industry experts to support your professional development.
